Package edu.ncsu.csc216.pack_scheduler.user

Class Student

java.lang.Object
edu.ncsu.csc216.pack_scheduler.user.User
edu.ncsu.csc216.pack_scheduler.user.Student
All Implemented Interfaces:
Comparable<Student>
public class Student extends User implements Comparable<Student>
Student is a model class which represents a student in the PackScheduler system. The Student object encapsulates field to uniquely identify each student and store useful information about the student. This information includes:
  • first name of the student.
  • last name of the student.
  • unity id of the student (unique identifier).
  • email of the student.
  • hashed password.
  • max credits the student can take.
The object provides getters and setters (with proper validation) for the mentioned fields. In addition to an ability to check if the Student can be enrolled in a particular Course.
Author:
Eswar Talasila, Maxim Shelepov

    • compareTo

      public int compareTo(Student s)
      Compares this Student object to another Student object for ordering based on last name, first name, and unity ID. This method defines the natural ordering for Student objects. Students are first compared based on their last names in lexicographical order. If the last names are equal, the comparison proceeds to compare their first names. If the first names are also equal, the comparison is based on their unity IDs. This ordering allows a collection of Student objects to be sorted by last name, and in cases of last name equality, further sorted by first name and unity ID.
      Specified by:
      compareTo in interface Comparable<Student>
      Parameters:
      s - the Student object to compare to
      Returns:
      a negative integer, zero, or a positive integer if this Student object is less than, equal to, or greater than the specified Student object, respectively, based on the last name, first name, and unity ID.
